definition: woods/forest/CL:片[pian4]/circle(s) (i.e. specific group of people)/a collection (of similar things)

son/child/seed/egg/small thing/1st earthly branch: 11 p.m.-1 a.m., midnight, 11th solar month (7th December to 5th January), year of the Rat/Viscount, fourth of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/ancient Chinese compass point: 0° (north)
it takes all sorts (to make a world) (idiom)
pinyin: lin2 zi5 da4 le5 , shen2 me5 niao3 dou1 you3

sentences.english: Between the woods and frozen lake.
Hunting is not allowed in this part of the woods.
sentences.chinese: 在这片林子里，不允许打猎。

sentences.english: It is a caseof not being able to see the forest for the trees.
sentences.chinese: 这就是一个只看到树而看不见林子的情况。

sentences.english: I'm going into the woods to cool off.
sentences.chinese: 我想进树林子里去凉快一下。

sentences.english: He is thought to be hiding in the woods.
sentences.chinese: 人们认为他躲在林子里。

sentences.english: Suddenly I have got the idea, to hunt rabbits in the woods.
sentences.chinese: 突然，我有了这个想法，去林子里去猎取野兔子。

sentences.english: From the green steeples of the piny wood;
sentences.chinese: 松树林子里，从那碧绿的树梢。

sentences.english: Lin Zijun in order not to expose the identity of it.
sentences.chinese: 林子君为了不暴露身份，忍气吞声。

sentences.english: At the edge of the world there was a narrow fringe of forest.
sentences.chinese: 一片窄窄的林子就在这个世界的边缘。

sentences.english: He really does own his wood, this able chap.
sentences.chinese: 他的林子确实是属于他的，这个能干的家伙。

sentences.english: Rabbit ran into the woods and disappeared.
sentences.chinese: 小兔跑进树林子，不见了。

sentences.english: But do not stray far into the wood.
sentences.chinese: 可是别在林子里走得太远。

sentences.english: Kentucky corn is what Jed makes back in the woods.
sentences.chinese: 杰德在林子后私酿的酒就是玉米威士忌。

sentences.english: At the end of the wood, the path diverges to the northwest.
sentences.chinese: 在林子的尽头，小径转向西北方向。

sentences.english: This path through the woods gets muddy on occasion.
sentences.chinese: 穿过林子的这条小径有时侯会变得泥泞不堪。
